summary:
8. Expresses concern at the security situation, welcomes MICOPAX efforts, and calls on countries and organizations to improve security;

9. Calls on parties to allow humanitarian access and protect civilians;

10. Stresses the Government's responsibility to maintain law and order, promote security, and protect civilians;

11. Urges the Government to respect freedom of expression and assembly, and engage in dialogue with opposition parties;

12. Underlines the need for a credible SSR strategy and cooperation from armed groups in DDR processes;

13. Strongly condemns human rights and humanitarian law violations, particularly by the LRA;

14. Demands prevention of child recruitment, and protection and treatment of released children;

15. Calls on parties to identify and release forcefully recruited persons, especially children, and prevent sexual violence;

16. Urges the Government to investigate human rights violations and bring perpetrators to justice;

17. Welcomes BINUCA's efforts to encourage LRA fighters' defection and support repatriation and reintegration;

18. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
